The paper discusses self-stabilizing overlay networks, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also focuses on searchability in these networks, which is a key aspect of network protocols and falls under the Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also deals with fault tolerance and recovery, which are important topics in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper introduces a set of primitives for manipulating overlay networks, which is a topic in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the generic search protocol, which is a distributed algorithm and falls under the Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed Systems) sub-category.
